Durban - A man was shot dead and a policeman was wounded in a brazen shooting incident in Hammarsdale, KwaZulu-Natal. Initially the PCCA WhatsApp group and other social media groups stated it was an attempted carjacking and that the victim was shot in the abdomen and through the cheeks on Thursday afternoon. The vehicle was not taken. Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, a KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, explained that at 15:50 a police officer was with his brother in-law in Hammarsdale. He said they were sitting under a tree when they were approached by two men. Both did not know the men. "The men informed them that they were looking for missing cattle. The men asked them for water. While still chatting one of the men allegedly drew a gun. He opened fire, fatally wounding the 59-year-old man. The officer sustained injuries and was taken to hospital for medical attention," Zwane said. Charges of murder and attempted murder were opened atÂ Hammarsdale police station for investigation. Daily News